&lt;p style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Shifting cultivation in the world:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Milpa in Central America.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Chitemene or Tavy in Africa.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Chena in Sri Lanka.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Conuco in&amp;nbsp;Venzuela.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Roca in Brazil.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Masole&amp;nbsp;in Central Africa.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Ladang&amp;nbsp;in Indonesia.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Ray in Vietnam.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Commercial farming:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In&amp;nbsp;commercial farming,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;crops are grown and animals are reared for sale in the market.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;area cultivated and the amount of capital&amp;nbsp;used is large.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Most of the work is done by machines.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Commercial farming includes commercial&amp;nbsp;grain farming, mixed farming and plantation agriculture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Subsistence&amp;nbsp;farming:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Subsistence farming&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (26, 26, 26);&quot;&gt;, a form of farming&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (26, 26, 26);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;in which nearly all of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;crops or livestock raised are used to maintain the farmer and the farmer&amp;rsquo;s family&lt;/span&gt;, leaving&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;little, if any, surplus for sale or trade.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Its characteristics are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;no surplus, distress sale, less or no use of fertilizers etc.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Plantation farming:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Plantations are a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;type of commercial farming&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;where a single&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;crop of tea, coffee, sugarcane, cashew, rubber, banana or cotton are grown.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A large amount of&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;labor and capital&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;are required.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The produce may be processed on the farm itself or in nearby factories.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The development of a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;transport network is thus essential&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;for such farming.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt; 67,956 km.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Indian Railways is one of the largest railway networks in the world and connects almost all parts of India through its extensive network of tracks.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As of March 2020, the total route length of the Indian Railways is 67,956 km, which includes both broad gauge and meter gauge tracks.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Indian Railways has 18 zones and more than 7,000 stations, making it an integral part of the country&amp;#39;s transportation infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Indian Railways also operates several luxury and tourist trains, such as the Palace on Wheels and the Maharaja Express, which offer a unique and memorable travel experience to passengers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The first opulent tourist train in India is called The Palace on Wheels.&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;In an effort to boost tourism in Rajasthan, the Indian Railways and the Rajasthan Tourism Development Corporation jointly launched it.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;In 1982, the train was introduced.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Heritage Palace on Wheels is the new name for the train.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Indian Railway Catering and Tourism Corporation is the owner and operator of the opulent tourist train known as the Maharajas&amp;#39; Express.&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Between October and April, it operates four routes through North-West and Central India, with a primary focus on Rajasthan.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shamsuddin Iltutmish.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&lt;strong&gt; Iqta&amp;nbsp;System or Iqtadari System&lt;/strong&gt; was introduced by &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shamsuddin Iltutmish&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;of&amp;nbsp;the &lt;strong&gt;Delhi Sultanate.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Iqtadari System&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;was a powerful instrument for&amp;nbsp;centralization.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Iqtadari System was based&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;on the division of territories between Sultans and Nobility.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The land was divided into small tracts and they were given to the nobles, the officers, and the soldiers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The areas directly under Sultan came to be&amp;nbsp;known as &lt;strong&gt;Khalisa&lt;/strong&gt; and the rest of the areas were known as &lt;strong&gt;Iqra.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Regin of Iltumish -&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;1211-1236 AD.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Iltumish was son-in-law of Aibak.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;He was a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Turkic slave.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;He was the&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;greatest of the Slave rulers&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of Delhi.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Slave dynasty was established by&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Qutb-us-din Aibak.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Dynasty lasted from&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;1206 to 1290.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It was the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;first of the dynasties&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;to rule as Sultanate in Delhi.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This dynasty was succeeded by&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Khilji Dynasty.&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Ctrl + C&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + C is the universal shortcut key for copying text or objects in Windows.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is widely used in various applications such as Word, Excel, browsers, and others.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This command replicates the selected text or object to the clipboard without removing it from the original location.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Users can then paste the copied content elsewhere using the Ctrl + V shortcut.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + V:&lt;/strong&gt; Used to paste the copied or cut content from the clipboard.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + P:&lt;/strong&gt; Shortcut key for printing documents or files.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + X:&lt;/strong&gt; Used to cut selected text or objects, removing them from their original location and placing them on the clipboard.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clipboard:&lt;/strong&gt; A temporary storage area in Windows used for storing copied or cut content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Option 4.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;69th &lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Constitutional Amendment Act of 1991&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;69 Amendment Constitutional Amendment Act of 1991 designated the&lt;strong&gt; Union Territory of Delhi as the National Capital Territory of Delhi.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The 69th Amendment act of the&lt;strong&gt; Indian Constitution granted special status to Delhi i&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;n 1991&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;it was&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;declared the National Capital Territory.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It &lt;strong&gt;created a state assembly and council &lt;/strong&gt;of ministers for the state.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aditya Nath Jha became the first Lieutenant Governor &lt;/strong&gt;of Delhi under the act.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Article 239AA of the Constitution gave the status of Union Territory to Delhi.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assam Accord&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Assam Accord&lt;/strong&gt; was signed on &lt;strong&gt;15 August 1985&lt;/strong&gt; between the Government of India and leaders of the Assam Movement.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The accord aimed to address the issue of &lt;strong&gt;illegal immigration&lt;/strong&gt; into Assam, particularly from neighboring countries like Bangladesh.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Citizenship (Amendment) Act, 1985 was introduced as a result of the Assam Accord, amending the Citizenship Act, 1955.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Assam Accord defined specific cut-off dates for identifying and deporting &lt;strong&gt;illegal immigrants&lt;/strong&gt;. People who entered Assam after &lt;strong&gt;March 24, 1971&lt;/strong&gt; were to be identified and deported.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The accord also provided for the protection of &lt;strong&gt;Assamese cultural identity&lt;/strong&gt;, language, and heritage while addressing the concerns of indigenous communities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It led to the establishment of mechanisms to detect and deport foreigners, including the formation of &lt;strong&gt;Foreigners&amp;#39; Tribunals&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Assam Accord continues to be a cornerstone in debates surrounding &lt;strong&gt;citizenship and immigration policies&lt;/strong&gt; in India.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Shimla Agreement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Shimla Agreement&lt;/strong&gt; was signed on &lt;strong&gt;2 July 1972&lt;/strong&gt; between &lt;strong&gt;India and Pakistan&lt;/strong&gt; following the Indo-Pak war of 1971.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It aimed at restoring peace and normalizing relations between the two nations.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The agreement established the &lt;strong&gt;Line of Control (LoC)&lt;/strong&gt; in Jammu and Kashmir.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It holds significance in the context of India&amp;#39;s foreign policy and relations with Pakistan but is unrelated to the issue of citizenship or immigration.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Indo-Sri Lanka Pact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Indo-Sri Lanka Pact&lt;/strong&gt;, also known as the &lt;strong&gt;Rajiv Gandhi-Jayewardene Accord&lt;/strong&gt;, was signed in &lt;strong&gt;1987&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It aimed at resolving the &lt;strong&gt;Sri Lankan Civil War&lt;/strong&gt; and ensuring the rights of Tamil minorities in Sri Lanka.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The pact led to the deployment of the &lt;strong&gt;Indian Peace Keeping Force (IPKF)&lt;/strong&gt; in Sri Lanka.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;While significant in the context of international relations, it is not connected to the citizenship issues addressed by the Assam Accord.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kashmir Agreement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The term &lt;strong&gt;Kashmir Agreement&lt;/strong&gt; often refers to attempts or discussions to resolve the issue of &lt;strong&gt;Jammu and Kashmir&lt;/strong&gt; between India and Pakistan.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It pertains to territorial disputes and regional autonomy rather than citizenship or immigration-related concerns.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It holds importance in the geopolitical context but is unrelated to the Assam Accord or the Citizenship (Amendment) Act, 1985.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Graphic Card&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Central Processing Unit (CPU)&lt;/strong&gt; primarily consists of three main components: &lt;strong&gt;Arithmetic Logic Unit (ALU), Control Unit (CU), and Registers&lt;/strong&gt;. These work together to process data and execute instructions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;Graphic Card&lt;/strong&gt; is a separate hardware component designed to handle the rendering of images, videos, and 3D graphics, and is not a part of the CPU.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Arithmetic Logic Unit (ALU)&lt;/strong&gt; is responsible for performing arithmetic and logical operations within the CPU.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Control Unit (CU)&lt;/strong&gt; directs the flow of data within the CPU, coordinating the activities of other components.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registers&lt;/strong&gt; are small storage locations within the CPU that hold data, instructions, and addresses temporarily during computation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Central Processing Unit (CPU):&lt;/strong&gt; Often referred to as the &amp;quot;brain&amp;quot; of the computer, the CPU performs all processing tasks and executes instructions from programs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Graphic Card:&lt;/strong&gt; Also known as a GPU (Graphics Processing Unit), it is optimized for rendering images and videos. It is essential for tasks such as gaming, video editing, and 3D modeling, but operates independently of the CPU.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registers:&lt;/strong&gt; These are high-speed storage units located inside the CPU. Examples include the accumulator, instruction register, and program counter.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Control Unit (CU):&lt;/strong&gt; The CU interprets instructions from programs and directs the operation of the CPU and other components such as memory and I/O devices.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ALU (Arithmetic Logic Unit):&lt;/strong&gt; Performs mathematical calculations (addition, subtraction, multiplication, division) and logical operations (AND, OR, NOT) within the CPU.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Margins&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Margins&lt;/strong&gt; feature in MS Word allows users to set the blank space between the text and the edges of the page.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Margins can be adjusted by navigating to &lt;strong&gt;Layout &amp;gt; Margins&lt;/strong&gt;, where predefined options like Normal, Narrow, Wide, and custom settings are available.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Changing the margins affects the document layout, helping users manage text density and page appearance efficiently.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Proper margin settings are crucial for ensuring readability, consistency, and adherence to document formatting standards, such as those required for academic or professional submissions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;MS Word allows users to set margins individually for each side of the page: top, bottom, left, and right.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Page Layout Tab in MS Word:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Page Layout tab includes essential formatting options like Margins, Orientation, Size, Columns, and Page Borders.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It enables users to customize the overall appearance and structure of the document.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other Margin Types:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;MS Word allows for the creation of &lt;strong&gt;gutter margins&lt;/strong&gt;, which provide extra space for binding documents.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Mirror margins are used for documents intended for double-sided printing, ensuring symmetry between facing pages.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Document Orientation:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Orientation options (Portrait and Landscape) can complement margin settings to optimize document appearance.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Portrait orientation is vertical, while Landscape orientation is horizontal.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Page Borders vs. Margins:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;While margins define blank space around text, &lt;strong&gt;Page Borders&lt;/strong&gt; add decorative or functional lines around the page&amp;rsquo;s edges.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Page Borders are customizable under the Design tab in MS Word.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Importance of Margins:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Proper margins improve visual appeal and help maintain a professional appearance in documents.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;They are crucial for printing, ensuring text does not get cut off or overlap binding areas.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chhotanagpur Plateau&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;River Damodar&lt;/strong&gt; flows through the &lt;strong&gt;Chhotanagpur Plateau&lt;/strong&gt;, which is located in the eastern part of India, primarily in the state of &lt;strong&gt;Jharkhand&lt;/strong&gt;, with some parts extending to &lt;strong&gt;West Bengal&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Chhotanagpur Plateau is rich in &lt;strong&gt;mineral resources&lt;/strong&gt; such as coal, iron ore, mica, and bauxite, making it a significant region for mining activities in India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The River Damodar is often referred to as the &lt;strong&gt;Sorrow of Bengal&lt;/strong&gt; due to its history of frequent flooding, causing damage to agricultural lands and settlements.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Several dams and reservoirs have been constructed in this region to control floods and harness the river for &lt;strong&gt;hydroelectric power generation&lt;/strong&gt;. These include the &lt;strong&gt;Panchet, Maithon, and Konar dams&lt;/strong&gt;, which are part of the Damodar Valley Corporation (DVC).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Chhotanagpur Plateau is characterized by its &lt;strong&gt;rugged terrain&lt;/strong&gt;, with an average elevation ranging between &lt;strong&gt;600 to 700 meters&lt;/strong&gt;. It is composed of &lt;strong&gt;gneissic and granite rocks&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The plateau is an important geographical feature that influences the drainage pattern of rivers, including the &lt;strong&gt;Damodar River&lt;/strong&gt;, which flows through its valleys.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The tributaries of the Damodar River, such as the &lt;strong&gt;Barakar, Konar, and Bokaro rivers&lt;/strong&gt;, also originate in or flow through the Chhotanagpur Plateau.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deccan Plateau&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Deccan Plateau&lt;/strong&gt; is located in southern India and is known for its large size, covering multiple states including &lt;strong&gt;Maharashtra, Karnataka, Telangana, Andhra Pradesh, and Tamil Nadu&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is bounded by the &lt;strong&gt;Western Ghats&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Eastern Ghats&lt;/strong&gt;, and the &lt;strong&gt;Satpura Range&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Deccan Plateau is rich in &lt;strong&gt;black soil&lt;/strong&gt;, which is ideal for cultivating cotton.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Major rivers like the &lt;strong&gt;Godavari, Krishna, and Kaveri&lt;/strong&gt; originate from or flow through this plateau.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Malwa Plateau&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Malwa Plateau&lt;/strong&gt; is located in the western part of India, mainly in &lt;strong&gt;Madhya Pradesh&lt;/strong&gt;, with some parts extending into &lt;strong&gt;Rajasthan&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This plateau is known for its &lt;strong&gt;fertile black soil&lt;/strong&gt;, which supports the cultivation of crops like cotton and soybean.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The region is drained by rivers such as the &lt;strong&gt;Chambal, Mahi, and Betwa&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meghalaya Plateau&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Meghalaya Plateau&lt;/strong&gt;, also known as the &lt;strong&gt;Shillong Plateau&lt;/strong&gt;, is located in northeastern India, primarily in the state of &lt;strong&gt;Meghalaya&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is rich in &lt;strong&gt;limestone and coal deposits&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This plateau is characterized by its &lt;strong&gt;high rainfall&lt;/strong&gt;, with places like Cherrapunji and Mawsynram receiving some of the highest rainfall in the world.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Major rivers originating from this plateau include the &lt;strong&gt;Barak and Umiam rivers&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p data-end=&quot;57&quot; data-start=&quot;0&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pakistan&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p data-end=&quot;57&quot; data-start=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;284&quot; data-start=&quot;78&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Article 6&lt;/strong&gt; of the &lt;strong&gt;Indian Constitution&lt;/strong&gt; addresses the citizenship of persons who migrated to India from &lt;strong&gt;Pakistan&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;605&quot; data-start=&quot;482&quot;&gt;This provision specifically applies to individuals who were born in undivided India and moved to India after the partition in &lt;strong&gt;1947&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;692&quot; data-start=&quot;610&quot;&gt;It grants &lt;strong&gt;Indian citizenship&lt;/strong&gt; to those who migrated from Pakistan before &lt;strong&gt;July 19, 1948&lt;/strong&gt;, provided they or either of their parents were born in undivided India and had been residing in India since migration.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;1041&quot; data-start=&quot;850&quot;&gt;For those who migrated after &lt;strong&gt;July 19, 1948&lt;/strong&gt;, Indian citizenship is granted if they registered themselves as citizens of India under the prescribed procedure.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;1162&quot; data-start=&quot;1046&quot;&gt;The provision also specifies that the registration process must be conducted by an officer appointed by the Government of India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;1560&quot; data-start=&quot;1323&quot;&gt;This article is part of the broader framework of the Constitution that defines citizenship at the commencement of the Constitution.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;1654&quot; data-start=&quot;1565&quot;&gt;It aims to address the displacement and migration caused by the partition of India, ensuring legal recognition of citizenship for affected individuals.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;2112&quot; data-start=&quot;2076&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Pakistan&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Historical Context:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;2410&quot; data-start=&quot;2195&quot;&gt;The partition of India in &lt;strong&gt;1947&lt;/strong&gt; led to large-scale migration between India and Pakistan due to religious and communal reasons.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;2684&quot; data-start=&quot;2415&quot;&gt;Millions of people moved across borders, creating a significant need for a legal framework to grant citizenship to migrants.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Provisions under Article 6:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;2860&quot; data-start=&quot;2735&quot;&gt;Migrants who entered India before &lt;strong&gt;July 19, 1948&lt;/strong&gt;, and lived in India since migration automatically qualified for citizenship.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3071&quot; data-start=&quot;2865&quot;&gt;Those who migrated after this date were required to register themselves with the appropriate authority to obtain Indian citizenship.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3250&quot; data-start=&quot;3076&quot;&gt;The registration process required proof of residence in India and verification by the appointed officer.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Legislative Acts:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3402&quot; data-start=&quot;3301&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Citizenship Act of 1955&lt;/strong&gt; further elaborates on the provisions of Article 6, detailing the process of acquiring Indian citizenship by migrants from Pakistan.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;3580&quot; data-start=&quot;3407&quot;&gt;The act also specifies other modes of acquiring citizenship, such as birth, descent, registration, and naturalization.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Features of Article 6:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;4636&quot; data-start=&quot;4411&quot;&gt;Article 6 was designed to provide a legal framework for determining citizenship for individuals affected by the partition.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;4761&quot; data-start=&quot;4641&quot;&gt;It ensures that people who migrated from Pakistan due to religious or political persecution are given the right to Indian citizenship.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impact of Partition on Citizenship:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;5043&quot; data-start=&quot;4817&quot;&gt;The partition led to the displacement of millions of people, necessitating legal measures to address their citizenship status.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;5259&quot; data-start=&quot;5048&quot;&gt;Article 6 played a crucial role in integrating migrants into the socio-political framework of India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Planning Commission&amp;#39;s suggestions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The National Development Council (NDC) was established in &lt;strong&gt;1952&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Its creation was based on the recommendations and suggestions of the Planning Commission of India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The NDC aims to &lt;strong&gt;strengthen and mobilize the effort and resources of the nation in support of the Plan&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It provides a platform for discussing issues related to social and economic development and ensures the balanced and rapid economic growth of India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The NDC includes the Prime Minister, Union Cabinet Ministers, Chief Ministers of all states, and members of the Planning Commission.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Planning Commission of India&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Established in 1950 by a resolution of the Government of India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It was tasked with formulating India&amp;#39;s Five-Year Plans and assessing the country&amp;#39;s resources.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;In 2015, it was replaced by the NITI Aayog (National Institution for Transforming India).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Five-Year Plans&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;These are centralized and integrated national economic programs.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The first Five-Year Plan was launched in 1951, focusing on the agricultural sector.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The plans are aimed at improving the standard of living and achieving economic growth.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NITI Aayog&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Replaced the Planning Commission in 2015.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It serves as the premier policy think tank of the Government of India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Aims to foster cooperative federalism through structured support initiatives and mechanisms.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;National Development Council (NDC)&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is not a statutory body but functions as an advisory body.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Its purpose is to strengthen and mobilize the effort and resources of the nation in support of the Plan.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It includes representatives from both the central and state governments.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;9.21&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;literacy rate&lt;/strong&gt; in India increased from &lt;strong&gt;64.8%&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;in 2001&lt;/strong&gt; to &lt;strong&gt;74.01% in 2011&amp;nbsp;(increase of 9.21%)&lt;/strong&gt;, according to Census data.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;male literacy rate&lt;/strong&gt; increased from&lt;strong&gt; 75.26% in 2001&lt;/strong&gt; to &lt;strong&gt;82.14% in 2011&lt;/strong&gt;, while the &lt;strong&gt;female literacy rate &lt;/strong&gt;increased from &lt;strong&gt;53.67% in 2001&lt;/strong&gt; to &lt;strong&gt;65.46% in 2011&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&lt;strong&gt; gap between male and female literacy rates&lt;/strong&gt; decreased from &lt;strong&gt;21.59% in 2001&lt;/strong&gt; to &lt;strong&gt;16.68% in 2011&lt;/strong&gt;, indicating a narrowing gender disparity in literacy.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The states of &lt;strong&gt;Kerala, Mizoram, and Tripura&lt;/strong&gt; had the &lt;strong&gt;highest literacy rates in 2011,&lt;/strong&gt; while &lt;strong&gt;Bihar, Arunachal Pradesh, and Rajasthan &lt;/strong&gt;had the &lt;strong&gt;lowest literacy rates&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The increase in literacy rates can be attributed to&lt;strong&gt; various government initiatives and programs &lt;/strong&gt;aimed at promoting &lt;strong&gt;education and literacy&lt;/strong&gt;, such as the&lt;strong&gt; Sarva Shiksha Abhiyan and the National Literacy Mission&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Higher levels of education and awareness&lt;/strong&gt;, as well as improvements in infrastructure and access to educational facilities, have also contributed to the increase in literacy rates.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Census data on literacy rates is crucial for &lt;strong&gt;policymakers and educators&lt;/strong&gt; to &lt;strong&gt;assess the progress of literacy&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;initiatives and plan&lt;/strong&gt; for future interventions to further improve literacy levels in India.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Jawaharlal Nehru&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

