&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Education.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Right to Education&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;was made&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;a fundamental right by the 86th Constitutional Amendment Act 2002&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;86th Constitutional Amendment Act 2002 added &lt;strong&gt;Article 21 A&lt;/strong&gt; which declares that the state shall provide free and &lt;strong&gt;compulsory education to all children of age six to fourteen years.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It has made only elementary education a fundamental right but not professional of higher education.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;For its implementation Parliament passed the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Right of Children to Free and Compulsory Education Act in 2009&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This act is also known as the Right of Children to Free and Compulsory Education Act because of its provision of, &amp;ldquo;the fundamental right of every child between the ages of 6 to 14 with specifies minimum norms in elementary schools.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The RTE Act of the Parliament of India was&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;enacted on 4 August 2009 and came into effect from 1st April 2010.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Earlier the right was there in the constitution under article 45 in Parts IV under the directive principle of state policy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + V&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The keyboard shortcut &lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + V&lt;/strong&gt; is used to &amp;#39;Paste&amp;#39; copied content from the clipboard in most Windows applications.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Other common keyboard shortcuts include &lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + C&lt;/strong&gt; for copying, &lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + X&lt;/strong&gt; for cutting, and &lt;strong&gt;Ctrl + Z&lt;/strong&gt; for undoing the last action.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;These shortcuts are widely used across various applications to enhance productivity and streamline workflow.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Learning and using keyboard shortcuts can significantly speed up your tasks and improve efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Keyboard shortcuts are combinations of keys that provide an alternative way to do something that you&amp;rsquo;d typically do with a mouse.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;They are especially useful for repetitive tasks, reducing the time required to switch between the keyboard and mouse.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Most operating systems and software applications support a wide range of keyboard shortcuts, and they can often be customized to suit individual preferences.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Using keyboard shortcuts can also help reduce the risk of repetitive strain injuries by minimizing the amount of movement needed to perform tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
